Test Scenarios for Writing a Post in Linked in

Test Scenarios: Desktop
Test Scenario 1: Check the Start a post section block at the top of the Home screen
Test Scenario 2: Check the Create a post popup redirection
Test Scenario 3: Check the Privacy filter functionality
Test Scenario 4: Check the content input box functionalities
Test Scenario 5: Check the Emoji feature functionality
Test Scenario 6: Check the Media attachment options functionalities
Test Scenario 7: Check the Comment filter functionality
Test Scenario 8: Check the user is able to post correctly
Test Scenario 9: Check the Schedule post functionality
Test Scenario 10: Check the close Create post functionality

Test Scenarios: Desktop
Test Scenario 1: Check the Start a post icon at the quick access belt of the mobile Home screen
Test Scenario 2: Check the Create a post popup redirection
Test Scenario 3: Check the Privacy filter functionality
Test Scenario 4: Check the content input box functionalities
Test Scenario 5: Check the Add Background feature in the content input box
Test Scenario 6: Check the Media attachment options functionalities
Test Scenario 7: Check the Comment filter functionality
Test Scenario 8: Check the user is able to post correctly
Test Scenario 9: Check the Schedule post functionality
